Microsoft.Data.SqlClient is the recommended SQL Client library for .NET Core and .NET Standard applications. Some reasons to use Microsoft.Data.SqlClient over System.Data.SqlClient are:

- It's built to be cross-platform, so it works on .NET Core which runs on Linux, macOS and Windows. System.Data.SqlClient only works on Windows.
- It has better performance than System.Data.SqlClient.
- It supports newer SQL Server features that System.Data.SqlClient does not.

